My focus has shifted to the "Internal Project" category, leaning toward this as the best fit. Analyzing the ticket, phrases like "snow dashboard not working" and "wonder cube dash board" point to an internal tool. Though "Access" remains a possibility, the core complaint is functionality-based. Reclassifying as "Miscellaneous" is a backup; the project angle is most relevant. I'm now fully committed to "Internal Project." Phrases like "snow dashboard" and "wonder cube dash board" point strongly to internal tools, not general applications. While "Miscellaneous" remains an option, "Internal Project" is a better fit given the internal system context. The system failing is the heart of the matter.
